Section 1:
1 L.D. 1461
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 EDUCATION AND CULTURAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 953, L.D. 1461, “An Act to Prohibit
10 School Boards from Implementing or Enforcing Mask Mandates”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Prohibit School Boards from Implementing or Enforcing Mask Mandates
13 Unless Directed to Adopt a Mask Mandate by a State or Local Health Authority'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in §6558 in subsection 2 in the first line (page 1, line 8 in
15 L.D.) by striking out the following: "A" and inserting the following: 'Except as provided in
16 subsection 3, a'
17 Amend the bill in section 1 in §6558 by striking out all of subsections 3 and 4 (page 1,
18 lines 10 to 14 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
19 '3. Exception. A school board may adopt a mask mandate upon direction from a state
20 or local health authority. A mask mandate adopted under this subsection must include
21 provisions that masks worn by students must be appropriate for a school setting and fit-
22 tested by a health care professional.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment provides that a school board may adopt a mask mandate upon
2277 direction from a state or local health authority and requires that such a mandate include
2288 provisions related to the type and fit of masks worn by students. The amendment also
2299 removes the provisions of the bill related to enforcement and penalties for a school board
3300 that implements or enforces a mask mandate.
Page 1 - 132LR1583(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
